com.innowhere.jnieasy.core.typedec
Interface NativeFieldMethodSignature

All Superinterfaces:
NativeBehaviorSignature
All Known Subinterfaces:
NativeInstanceFieldMethodSignature, NativeStaticFieldMethodSignature
public interface NativeFieldMethodSignature
extends NativeBehaviorSignature

The NativeFieldMethodSignature interface represents the native signature declaration of native field-methods. A field-method signature is the native signature of a special native method oriented to get and set values of a field. This field may be a Java field (static or instance) or a DLL exported C field (only static).

The Java signature (and analogous in C) is:

public [static] FieldType fieldName(int opcode,FieldType value)
The opcode is the operation code, GET, SET, or GET_SET as defined in NativeFieldMethod

The native declaration of value parameter is identical to return type.

Author:
Jose M. Arranz Santamaria
See Also:
NativeSignatureManager.decFieldMethod(Class,Object,int)
